<item>
            <title>[SLING-9730] Scheduler job mapping doesn&apos;t work correctly for lambdas.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-9730</link>
                <project id="12310710" key="SLING">Sling</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When scheduling a job that is a Runnable the mapping from job to instance is done based on the class name. That is problematic in case of lambdas as the class name is not stable. We should use a key that is stable for all cases. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As we only have the object itself and the mapping needs to be stable across JVMs, the easiest mapping key seems to be the package name. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
